    rationale: "Cocaine is a potent vasoconstrictor that blocks the reuptake of norepinephrine (and dopamine) at sympathetic nerve terminals, causing prolonged alpha-adrenergic stimulation and intense vasoconstriction of the nasal mucosal vessels. This sustained vasoconstriction leads to ischemic necrosis of the nasal septal mucosa, perichondrium, and ultimately the cartilage itself, resulting in septal perforation. The perforation is typically midline and anterior. Cocaine does not dissolve cartilage chemically, cause vasculitis (though some granulomatous reactions can occur with levamisole-adulterated cocaine), or increase secretions. This mechanism is the same reason cocaine is used as a topical vasoconstrictor/anesthetic in nasal surgery \u2014 but chronic use causes ischemic damage.",
